&lt;p&gt;Are you and experienced, motivated and passionate Children’s nurse? Do you want to work within a supportive senior Children’s nursing team? Do you want to ensure all children get a high quality and safe service? Then this may be the right job for you. Children’s services in East Kent Hospitals has recently benefited from investment. Along with a Quality Improvement Matron, a Governance Matron and an increased Practice development team an exciting opportunity has arisen to increase the Acute Matrons from one to two. This will enable a more visible senior presence on each of our acute sites and will really strengthen the senior support to our dedicated team of children’s nurses, skilled Health care assistants’ nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lizzie Worthen, Deputy Head of Nursing Child Health&lt;/p&gt;
